ingredients_json: [{"ingredient": "cooking spray", "quantity": null, "unit": null}, {"ingredient": "ground venison", "quantity": "1", "unit": "pound"}, {"ingredient": "mushrooms", "quantity": "4", "unit": "button"}, {"ingredient": "celery", "quantity": "2", "unit": "ribs"}, {"ingredient": "onion", "quantity": "1", "unit": "medium"}, {"ingredient": "tomato", "quantity": "2", "unit": "cans"}, {"ingredient": "tomato", "quantity": "2", "unit": "tablespoons"}, {"ingredient": "garlic", "quantity": "1", "unit": "tablespoon"}, {"ingredient": "seasoning", "quantity": "2", "unit": "tablespoons"}, {"ingredient": "salt", "quantity": "1", "unit": "teaspoon"}, {"ingredient": "pepper", "quantity": "1", "unit": "teaspoon"}, {"ingredient": "parsley", "quantity": "1", "unit": "tablespoon"}, {"ingredient": "rice", "quantity": "1", "unit": null}, {"ingredient": "pepper", "quantity": "6", "unit": "bell"}, {"ingredient": "cheese", "quantity": "1", "unit": "cup"}]
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F, and spray large skillet with cooking spray. | In skillet, over medium heat, cook ground venison 5 minutes or until cooked almost through. | Add mushrooms, celery, and onions, and cook until vegetables are tender. | Stir in diced tomatoes, tomato paste, garlic powder, Italian seasoning, salt, pepper, parsley, and cooked rice. Cook for another 5 minutes or until the rice is warmed through. | Cut off tops of peppers and spoon out the ribs and seeds. Rinse. Lightly sprinkle the insides of peppers with salt and place in microwave-safe dish with 1/4 cup water. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave for 5 minutes or until peppers start to soften. | Transfer to 3-quart or 9×13-inch baking dish. Fill peppers with cooked meat and rice mixture. | Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 20 minutes or until peppers are tender and cheese is melted.
